      Vector3Dd getCurrentPosition()

    • getPreviousPosition

      Vector3Dd getPreviousPosition()
      Gets the previous position of this animated block. This value is updated after each tick/teleport and describes the location this animated block was at before it moved.
      Returns:
      The previous position of this animated block.

    • getPreviousTarget

      Removes the entity from the world.

    • getTicksLived

      int getTicksLived()
      Returns:
      The number of ticks this animated block has existed for.

    • getLocation

      ILocation getLocation()
      Returns:
      The current location of this entity.

      Note that this will not reflect the new location after the animated block is teleported until after the next tick.

    • getPosition

      Vector3Dd getPosition()
      Returns:
      The current position of this entity.

      Note that this will not reflect the new position after the animated block is teleported until after the next tick.

    • getStartPosition

      RotatedPosition getStartPosition()
      Returns:
      The starting position of this animated block.

    • getFinalPosition

      RotatedPosition getFinalPosition()
      Returns:
      The position where the block will be placed after the animation finishes.

    • getStartX

      default double getStartX()
      Returns:
      The x-coordinate of the location the block was first spawned at.

    • getStartY

      default double getStartY()
      Returns:
      The y-coordinate of the location the block was first spawned at.

    • getStartZ

      default double getStartZ()
      Returns:
      The z-coordinate of the location the block was first spawned at.

    • getRadius

      float getRadius()
      Returns:
      The radius this animated block had in relation to the engine when the animation first started.

    • isOnEdge

      boolean isOnEdge()
      Returns:
      True if this animated block is on the edge of the cuboid being animated.
